Key Match Events: Sadeera Samarawickrama won Man of the Match for his unbeaten 91 off 107 balls, with seven fours.
Sri Lanka registered its first win of the tournament. They have beaten Netherlands by five wickets and chased down the target (263/5) in 48.2 overs to win the game.
Sri Lanka has reached 171/3 after the end of 30 overs. They need 92 runs in last two overs with seven wickets in hand.
Pathum Nissanka completes his third half-century of the ICC Cricket World Cup 2023 off just 48 balls.
Sri Lanka finished first power-play at 56/2. They need another 207 runs in 40 overs.
